This assignment will help you interpret mathematical relationships both
algebraically and geometrically.

Create a function that takes a number (step) as an argument and returns the
number of matchsticks in that step. See step 1, 2 and 3 in the image above.
Take input from the user in the function parameter and return the output
using the return statement.

examples-
matchHouses(1) ➞ 6

matchHouses(4) ➞ 21
matchHouses(87) ➞ 436
?




function matchHouses(step) {
  // Base case: if step is 0, there are no matchsticks
  if (step === 0) {
    return 0;
  }

  // Each step after the first adds 5 matchsticks
  // The first step has 6 matchsticks
  return 5 * step + 1;
}

// Example usage:
console.log(matchHouses(1)); // ➞ 6
console.log(matchHouses(4)); // ➞ 21
console.log(matchHouses(87)); // ➞ 436
